      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "daeaa6b647697eddb451ef385e8e509662f69479",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2018-10-28 11:54:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified-1\n\nFailed enforced test review-ldiskfs on CentOS 7.0/x86_64 uploaded by Trevis Autotest from trevis-5vm1: https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/e6df3402-4beb-42f2-bf21-ef5e23538553 ran 4 tests.  1 tests failed: sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "164a12a7ca9876008d9313771e23b8843f286500",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 655,
        "name": "Arshad Hussain",
        "email": "arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com",
        "username": "arshad512"
      },
      "date": "2018-10-28 12:34:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas, Thanks to you!, James and others for review. Without the reviews this would not be possible.\n\nYou did mention to check open files that i do before taking up the file. Eg file:<file> is:open branch:master\n\nI have a rudimentary script to check the 'checkpatch' errors. Once this script report the error I go and manually inspect if change are required or not. This script does not catch everything, but it gives hint that this file needs to be inspected. \n\nI only run this script on a single folder. Presently i am targeting obdclass folder and all files within in. \n\nThis is the script and it reports plenty of checkpatch warnings/errors. The script is ...\n\n#!/bin/bash\n\nfor folder in fld ldlm lmv mdc mgc nodist ofd osd-zfs ptlrpc target lfsck lod mdd mgs obdclass osc osp quota fid llite lov mdt  obdecho osd-ldiskfs ost scripts  utils\ndo\n\tfor file in $(ls lustre/$folder/*.c)\n\tdo\n\t\t./contrib/scripts/checkpatch.pl -f --no-tree $file | grep tabs 2>&1 >/dev/null\n\t\tif [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\n\t\t\techo \"Found tabs erron on file [$file]\" >> err.file\n\t\tfi\n\tdone\ndone\n\nWhat I meant is, there is about 150+ files to be fixed. However if you want some set of files that needs to be fix earlier please do let me know I will target them first. And I will try to finish off as much as I could.\n\nThanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
